Sentencas: A numerical technique for generating the solid oxide fuel cell composite electrode structure based on measurable starting parameters has been developed.
Titulo: Computation of TPB length, surface area and pore size from numerical reconstruction of composite solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: This method can be used to calculate all relevant electrode microstructural parameters.
Titulo: Computation of TPB length, surface area and pore size from numerical reconstruction of composite solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: The structures are formed of randomly distributed overlapping spheres with particle size distributions that match the particle sizes of actual ceramic powders.
Titulo: Computation of TPB length, surface area and pore size from numerical reconstruction of composite solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: In this work, the triple phase boundary length, internal surface area, pore size and the percolation of all relevant phases within the porous composite electrode were computed.
Titulo: Computation of TPB length, surface area and pore size from numerical reconstruction of composite solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: It was found that the triple phase boundary length computed for particles with real particle size distributions was as much as 40% lower compared to rnono-sized particles with the same mean particle sizes.
Titulo: Computation of TPB length, surface area and pore size from numerical reconstruction of composite solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Percolation thresholds were in the range of 30-40 vol% for solid phases and over 99% of pores were found to belong to a percolating network at porosities as low as 25%.
Titulo: Computation of TPB length, surface area and pore size from numerical reconstruction of composite solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: In addition, the average pore size was found to be 0.19 mu m for typical electrode compositions, smaller than what is commonly assumed and in certain circumstances, the distribution of pore sizes may place gas transport in the free molecular flow regime.
Titulo: Computation of TPB length, surface area and pore size from numerical reconstruction of composite solid oxide fuel cell electrodes
